"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `np.insert` function is used to insert values into an array along a specified axis. The `values` parameter should be shaped so that `arr[..., obj, ...] = values` is legal. In this case, the value `3` is being inserted into a float64 array, which will cause a type casting issue.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< arr = np.insert(arr, 1, 3, axis=1)\\n---\\n> arr = np.insert(arr, 1, 3.0, axis=1)\\n\"\n}"